            <title>[JDK-8313082] Enable CreateCoredumpOnCrash for testing in makefiles</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8313082</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The option&lt;br/&gt;
CreateCoredumpOnCrash&lt;br/&gt;
is enabled by default except the Windows client systems with release binaries.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
So it makes sense to switch it on explicitly on Windows for testing. It still could be redefined by adding &amp;#39;-XX-CreateCoredumpOnCrash&amp;#39; as vmoption if needed like for default setting.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
