                            <comment id="14599502" author="dholmes" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2023 19:35:42 -0700"  >I was suggesting we re-examine that but you&amp;#39;re right this is to protect users of games that crash frequently.</comment>
                            <comment id="14599421" author="lmesnik" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2023 10:58:17 -0700"  >As I remember the idea is to don&amp;#39;t save minidumps on Window 10,11 (client) OS. The crahses often happen because of 3rd party native libs bugs and non hotstpot issues and the minidumps just litter the disk.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Do you propose to remove the following code?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/master/src/hotspot/os/windows/os_windows.cpp#L1180&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openjdk/jdk/blob/master/src/hotspot/os/windows/os_windows.cpp#L1180&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
#ifndef ASSERT&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if (!os::win32::is_windows_server() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; FLAG_IS_DEFAULT(CreateCoredumpOnCrash)) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;jio_snprintf(buffer, buffsz, &amp;quot;Minidumps are not enabled by default on client versions of Windows&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;status = false;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
#endif</comment>
                            <comment id="14599116" author="dholmes" created="Tue, 25 Jul 2023 20:17:29 -0700"  >The notion of a &amp;quot;Windows client&amp;quot; machine seems out-of-touch these days, so it may make sense to look at changing this in hotspot.</comment>
